=Summary=

Laurence Cox:

"Can Democracy be Saved? is two books in one, and carries off the trick impressively. The first book is
a textbook of models of democracy – liberal, participatory, deliberative, electronic, global. As with
comparable textbooks, it is essentially a typology, organised around the different adjectives ... The second book is an account of how social movements practice democracy – both internally and in their pressure for wider political
and social democratisation."




